Items.Title: That this House note that 25 April 2007 marks the 92nd anniversary of the Gallipoli landings in Turkey during the First World War; and note that for the nine months following the landings the Australia and New Zealand Army Corps encoun
Items.CpdMotion: That this House note that 25 April 2007 marks the 92nd anniversary of the Gallipoli landings in Turkey during the First World War; and note that for the nine months following the landings the Australia and New Zealand Army Corps encountered not only a formidable opponent, but also extremely rugged terrain, and that this ultimately unsuccessful campaign saw New Zealand suffer a 57 percent casualty rate, with 2,721 dead, of whom 1,669 still lie on the Peninsula with no known grave.
